result.execSummary:
The defendant Adrian Michael Cullinan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Ignition Interlock Device Tampering/Failure to Install, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 347.413(1).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:43 p.m.  State by DA Andrew Christenson.  Defendant present with Attorney Barb Privat.

Attorney Privat recites the agreement - defendant plea to count 1 and 2 - DRI count 3.  DA concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY to counts 1 and 2.  Court finds each plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support each plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty as charged on counts 1 and 2 and orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Court DRI count 3.  Sentencing argument by DA.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Privat.  Statement by the defendant.  

Each count - Court sentences the defendant to 30 days county jail - if served to be consecutive to each other and consecutive to any other sentence, stayed and placed on probation for 2 years - concurrent to each other and concurrent to any other probation.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION - each count.
Abide with all other rulres/recommendations as imposed by the supervising agent.
Count 1 - Pay a $150.00 fine plus court costs.
Count 2 - Pay court costs.

Court adjourned at 2:53 p.m.
Plea/sentencing hearing on December 23, 2014 at 02:00 pm.

1:24 p.m.  State by DA Andrew Christenson.  NO appearance by the defendant.  Attorney Barb Privat present on behalf of the defendant.

Statement by Attorney Privat - offer has been made.

Court directs case be set for Plea/Sentencing and to be held in approximately thirty days - defendant must be personally present.

Court adjourned at 1:25 p.m.
Return date on November 17, 2014 at 01:00 pm.

2:07 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Privat, is willing to waive the preliminary hearing.  Defendant concurs.  

Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.  State files an information with the court.  Attorney Privat and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Privat enters a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of the defendant.  Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Court will set for status hearing.

Court adjourned at 2:09 p.m.
Status hearing on September 22, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.

2:55 p.m.  State by DA Andrew Christenson.  Defendant present via video from Green Lake County Jail with Attorney Barb Privat.

Attorney Privat confirms receipt of the complaint - waives reading.  Court makes statement regarding maximum penalties on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  

Court orders bond set at $250.00 cash with the conditions of:  Maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess/consume any alcohol, illegal drugs, or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.  

Attorney Privat waives time limits as to the preliminary hearing - defendant qualifies for PD representation.  Court directs Status Hearing to be held in approximately thirty days - put on Attorney Privat's calendar.

Court adjourned at 2:59 p.m.
